Added some olive oil to the tiny bit of butter, used shallots instead of onion, doubled the clams (half whole, half chopped) doubled the wine and clam liquid, and added a sprinkle of red pepper flakes, a spritz of lemon (don't use too much!) and a grating of Pecorino Romano with lots of black pepper. Tasty but not great. Might try with cream or creme fraiche (or nothing!) instead of the sour cream next time.

Rating: 4
I took a few ideas from other Linguine with Clam Sauce recipes along with review feedback and made cream sauce Linguine with Clams that both my mother in-law and my Wife loved. I don't cook enough but this was fabulous and easy for anyone to make. Here are the changes I made: - added thyme to the oil/marg/shallots/garlic saute. My wife is lactose intolerant. - if possible use fresh pasta clams and just cook them in the wine. - mix sour cream (lactose free), belsoy cream (soy), cayenne pepper, fresh ground pepper, salt, and some lemon rind (adds a nice element to the dish). - Once the clams are cooked, take the pan off the heat, add the sour cream mix while whisking to avoid separation. - Grate parmesan over the pot - Place back on head and add cornstarch if required to thicken if required. I needed it so that it would stick to linguine. Make sure that you use a wine that you will then drink with the food, it makes the food pop even more.

