Rating: 2
Who decided that clam sauce should be thick and creamy? This recipe has the basic idea down. Clam sauce should be more like a rich broth. Forget cream, sour cream, or (?)cornstarch. Use both butter and extra virgin olive oil, lots of wine and garlic, add some bottled clam juice, reduce liquid down to a broth with body. Add clams at the last minute. Fresh parsley only, preferably flat Italian. And adding fresh clams is awesome! Garnish with some fresh parmesan, more fresh parsley, and lemon wedges on the side.

