Rating: 2
This recipe was pretty good. To prevent the clams from getting tough, I added them to the sauce at the very end (I read this somewhere and it's true). I also mixed in the sour cream at the end. I also agree with the other reviewer that the sauce is a bit thin, so I added 1 tablespoon of cornstarch which made a nice, smooth thick sauce (if this is too thick for your taste, you can always thin it out with some milk or wine). Then, to make it less bland, I added white pepper and about 2 teaspoons of lemon juice to taste. Finally, the addition of fat-free parmesan cheese was the finishing touch!! Overall, a very easy and tasty dish.

